    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">A Comparative Study on the Modes of Disribution of Mutual Funds in Indbank Merchant Banking Services Limited, Chennai.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Vidya.D</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Mutual Funds<br />Indbank Merchant Banking Services</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">May-2012 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Publisher:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">SRM University</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">P5600</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">The purpose of this project is to study about the basic concepts in the area of mutual funds. The Securities and Exchange Board of India (Mutual Funds) Regulations, 1996 defines a mutual fund as a ‘a fund established in the form of a trust to raise money through the sale of units to the public or a section of the public under one or more schemes for investing in securities, including money market instruments’.
Mutual fund is a collective savings scheme. Mutual funds play an important role in mobilising the savings of small investors and channelising the same for productive ventures in the Indian economy. A mutual fund serves as a link between the investor and the securities market by mobilising savings from the investors and investing them in the securities market to generate returns.
The objectives of mutual funds are to provide continuous liquidity and higher yields with high degree of safety to investors. The various modes of distribution of mutual funds is done through the following types which are direct distribution of funds , Exchange Traded funds,
Selling or buying of mutual funds through broking network.This report gives a complete insight into modes of distribution of mutual funds.
Among these modes of distribution , direct distribution of funds, which is considered to be the existing strategy of Indbank Merchant Banking Services Limited, contributes major income to the company.
One of the latest development in Indbank Merchant Banking Services Limited, in the area of mutual fund distribution is Selling or Buying of Mutual funds through Broking Network whereby distribution is done using the broking account of the client but without the intervention of Stock Exchange.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">URI:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/9724">http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/9724</a></td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Appears in Collections:</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="/dspace/handle/123456789/9711">MBA-2012</a><br/></td></tr>
</table></center><br/>
